{"lemma":"طَوْفَيْ","slug":"طَوْفَيْ","root":"ط.#.ف","root_slug":"ط-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n27313"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to circulate, wander around"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tˤaw.wa.fa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27313","headword_ar":"طَوْفٌ","root":"Twf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbahu mina Al$~ayoTaAni TawofN","text_ar":"اَصَابَهُ مِنَ الشَّيْطَانِ طَوْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ifN","text_ar":"طَايِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ifN","text_ar":"طَايِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, and in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tyf","text_ar":"طيف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of float composed of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inflated water-skins bound together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"planks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid upon them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to have the form of a flat roof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used for embarking thereon upon the water and for carriage thereon"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wheat or other provisions and of men, and for the crossing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rivers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramavN","text_ar":"رَمَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes it is of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"timber:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing upon which large rivers are crossed, made of canes and of pieces of wood bound together, one upon another, and then bound round with ropes of the fibres or leaves of the palm-tree so as to be secure from its becoming unbound; after which it is used for embarking thereon and crossing, and sometimes it is laden with a load proportionate to its strength and its thickness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmapN","text_ar":"عَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaAfN","text_ar":"اَطْوَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bull"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawor","text_ar":"ثَوْر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around which turn the oxen in the treading"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ifN","text_ar":"طَايِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qilodN","text_ar":"قِلْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion of water for irrigation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is immediately added], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawofu","text_ar":"طَوْفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaSabi","text_ar":"القَصَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the quantity of water with which the canes are irrigated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul matter that comes forth from the child after suckling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Ahmar, Msb, TA:) and by a secondary application, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"human excrement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) in an absolute sense: (Msb:) what Er-Rághib says respecting it indicates that this is metonymical. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]}]}}